{"schemaVersion":1,"id":"53c56b01-c7f0-4d19-a982-825e275171f7","at":"2026-07-14T17:36:44.030Z","actor":{"kind":"user","name":"danvers"},"type":"todo.opened","payload":{"todo":{"id":"td-d9d78159-eb0d-4f09-96b0-4b7b356eba64","kind":"bug","status":"open","title":"StationEngine discards seedProviderAuth result; station auth failures aren't enriched like RunEngine's","detail":"RunEngine keeps authSeed.missingHint and uses it to turn a provider-side 'Authentication required' into a precise 'you're not authenticated (checked X)' message. StationEngine (post PR #58) calls seedProviderAuth(provider, isolatedConfigDir) but ignores the return value, so a station run that fails on auth still surfaces the opaque provider error. Mirror RunEngine: thread the AuthSeedResult into the failure path. Candidate for /code-review.","priority":20,"created":"2026-07-14","source":{"kind":"user","name":"danvers"}}}}
