{"schemaVersion":1,"id":"bdc84a56-420a-41fd-b309-05e9b3e31ebe","at":"2026-07-14T22:12:35.633Z","actor":{"kind":"user","name":"danvers"},"type":"todo.opened","payload":{"todo":{"id":"td-9a80a2bb-4888-46e4-a897-5854af886198","kind":"improvement","status":"open","title":"Overview surfaces the state machine instead of guiding the director to one next action","detail":"The bundle Overview (BundlePanel.tsx) stacks Request-review, Advance, and Move-back at equal weight, so a user must understand the whole machine to pick. guardStatus already knows the state -- compute and present the single recommended next step as the primary CTA (working -> Request review / Approve & advance; awaiting-review -> Approve), and demote the rest. Keystone of the gate-flow UX cleanup; several sibling improvements fall out of it.","priority":15,"created":"2026-07-14","source":{"kind":"user","name":"danvers"}}}}
{"schemaVersion":1,"id":"ff0f8134-a80f-4668-98a4-c04530348563","at":"2026-07-14T22:12:35.756Z","actor":{"kind":"user","name":"danvers"},"type":"todo.opened","payload":{"todo":{"id":"td-10df1afc-d3b0-4d8c-9041-4ffc7ab8fbc3","kind":"improvement","status":"open","title":"Decide whether human-authored stages (Frame/idea) need a review pair at all","detail":"On a hand-seeded idea the review pair is request-your-own-review -> approve-it -> advance: self-approval theater, no agent doer and no artifact to judge. Decision needed: drop the review pair for human-authored stage work (advance directly with a soft confirm) and surface the pair only when a station run produced an artifact worth reviewing. Affects the guard model in Machine/guardStatus; gates the rest of the redesign.","priority":15,"created":"2026-07-14","source":{"kind":"user","name":"danvers"}}}}
{"schemaVersion":1,"id":"43ed8e83-b89a-4bc8-9360-0f49dfb091f2","at":"2026-07-14T22:12:35.880Z","actor":{"kind":"user","name":"danvers"},"type":"todo.opened","payload":{"todo":{"id":"td-b925074f-7406-4a10-8d2d-91dc9c738b51","kind":"improvement","status":"open","title":"Overview leads with raw guard booleans (approved-for-forward false, gate-approved false) as status","detail":"The panel top-lines Stage/Substate/Guard: approved-for-forward false, gate-approved false -- internal telemetry shown as the primary status. A director cannot read approved-for-forward false. Replace with a plain-language status line (e.g. Drafting the idea / Ready for research once approved) and tuck the raw stage/substate/guard fields behind a Details disclosure for devs.","priority":20,"created":"2026-07-14","source":{"kind":"user","name":"danvers"}}}}
{"schemaVersion":1,"id":"62a34d75-9f8c-4cc7-b08a-bab94c2b2bbf","at":"2026-07-14T22:12:36.017Z","actor":{"kind":"user","name":"danvers"},"type":"todo.opened","payload":{"todo":{"id":"td-58dae81d-6e59-47de-9a19-66643bfb396a","kind":"improvement","status":"open","title":"Guard rejections leak the raw server error (event-type names + state jargon) into the viewer","detail":"Clicking Advance before the gate is met renders the server rejection verbatim: forward transition from \"idea\" requires an approved review (\"review.resolved\" with decision \"approve\" for state \"idea\") recorded since the last stage change. Leaks event types and machine vocab to a director. Map guard failures to a human sentence in the viewer (This needs an approved review before it can move to Research); keep the precise string for the CLI/--json.","priority":20,"created":"2026-07-14","source":{"kind":"user","name":"danvers"}}}}
{"schemaVersion":1,"id":"43db77e7-ec82-4315-a863-00c93bc80f3c","at":"2026-07-14T22:12:36.163Z","actor":{"kind":"user","name":"danvers"},"type":"todo.opened","payload":{"todo":{"id":"td-253e583c-ab1a-49b6-baac-9ff80c19e4a7","kind":"improvement","status":"open","title":"Advance is always-clickable-into-failure (the reachable-409 choice) -- a director is invited to hit a wall","detail":"BundlePanel keeps Advance clickable even when guardStatus predicts rejection -- the deliberate reachable-409 choice (see its docstring), built so a developer can exercise the guarded-transition path from the UI. For a real user this invites a failed click plus a scary red error. Make the primary CTA the allowed action; when advance is not yet possible, show what is needed instead of a clickable failure. Preserve the 409 path for tests/dev, not the default surface.","priority":20,"created":"2026-07-14","source":{"kind":"user","name":"danvers"}}}}
{"schemaVersion":1,"id":"28156ffa-f556-4e66-aaf9-e061eaf0be71","at":"2026-07-14T22:12:36.302Z","actor":{"kind":"user","name":"danvers"},"type":"todo.opened","payload":{"todo":{"id":"td-5e83da8c-d263-4b43-b271-323ab10ae2ca","kind":"improvement","status":"open","title":"Merge approve + advance into one action for the solo path","detail":"Approving only flips the forward guard; the user must then separately locate and click Advance. Collapse the common case to one action (Approve advances, or Approve & advance). Turns two-click gate theater into one click.","priority":20,"created":"2026-07-14","source":{"kind":"user","name":"danvers"}}}}
{"schemaVersion":1,"id":"7d8e9114-2d40-4d53-a3fa-40ad30d32268","at":"2026-07-14T22:12:36.436Z","actor":{"kind":"user","name":"danvers"},"type":"todo.opened","payload":{"todo":{"id":"td-ed4a9ef7-f942-4631-bbd4-39d5d3ee9cf2","kind":"improvement","status":"open","title":"Move-back is a co-equal panel; it should be a quiet undo affordance","detail":"The MOVE BACK section (earlier-stage dropdown + required reason + button) sits at the same visual weight as forward actions. It is an oops/undo, not a primary path. Demote to a quiet Move to an earlier stage link or overflow menu.","priority":30,"created":"2026-07-14","source":{"kind":"user","name":"danvers"}}}}
